%20no1/1982.htm |title=\u697d\u5929\u304c\u904b\u55b6\u3059\u308b\u30dd\u30fc\u30bf\u30eb\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8 \uff1a \u3010\u30a4\u30f3\u30d5\u30a9\u30b7\u30fc\u30af\u3011Infoseek |publisher=Msdb.hp.infoseek.co.jp |date=2000-01-01 |accessdate=2012-02-28}}</ref>\n\nIn 2003, ''Lionel Richie'' was re-released as part of a remaster series that saw two additional tracks added: a solo version of \"[[Endless Love (song)|Endless Love]]\" and an instrumental version of \"You Are\".\n[[Eagles (band)|Eagles]] member [[Joe Walsh]] provided the guitar solo for the song \"Wandering Stranger\".\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| title1          = Serves You Right\n| writer1         = {{flatlist|\n*John McClain\n*[[Greg Phillinganes]]\n*Lionel Richie}}\n| length1         = 5:14\n| title2          = Wandering Stranger\n| writer2         = Richie\n| length2         = 5:38\n| title3          = Tell Me\n| writer3         = {{flatlist|\n*Richie\n*[[David Foster]]}}\n| length3         = 5:32\n| title4          = [[My Love (Lionel Richie song)|My Love]]\n| writer4         = Richie\n| length4         = 4:08\n| title5          = Round and Round\n| writer5         = {{flatlist|\n*David Cochrane\n*Richie}}\n| length5         = 4:57\n| title6          = [[Truly (song)|Truly]]\n| writer6         = Richie\n| length6         = 3:26\n| title7          = [[You Are (Lionel Richie song)|You Are]]\n| writer7         = {{flatlist|\n*Brenda Harvey-Richie\n*Richie}}\n| length7         = 5:05\n| title8          = You Mean More to Me\n| writer8         = Richie\n| length8         = 3:08\n| title9          = Just Put Some Love in Your Heart\n| writer9         = Richie\n| length9         = 1:27\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = 2003 remaster bonus tracks\n| title10         = Endless Love\n| note10          = solo demo\n| writer10        = Richie\n| length10        = 3:58\n| title11         = You Are\n| note11          = instrumental\n| writer11        = {{flatlist|\n*Harvey-Richie\n*Richie}}\n| length11        = 5:06\n}}\n\n==In popular culture==\nIn a Season 3 episode of ''[[Friends]]'', the character, [[Chandler Bing|Chandler]] is seen holding a copy of this album and singing \"[[Endless Love (song)|Endless Love]]\". The song was not a part of this release; however, the song now appears on the 2003 remastered edition as one of two bonus tracks (as a solo performance only).  At the time, \"Endless Love\" was available only on the original soundtrack to the 1981 [[Endless Love (1981 film)|movie of the same name]] starring [[Brooke Shields]], as well as Richie's compilation ''[[Back to Front (Lionel Richie album)|Back to Front]]'' and Diana Ross's ''[[One Woman: The Ultimate Collection]]''.\n\n==Personnel==\n\n===Musicians===\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Lionel Richie]] \u2013 lead vocals, vocal arrangements, backing vocals (1, 2, 3, 5-8), acoustic piano (4, 6, 8), [[Rhodes piano|Fender Rhodes]] (7), rhythm arrangements (7)\n* [[Greg Phillinganes]] \u2013 Fender Rhodes (1), [[Roland Jupiter 8]] (1), [[Minimoog]] (1), arrangements (1)\n* [[Clarence McDonald]] \u2013 Fender Rhodes (2)\n* [[Michael Lang (musician)|Michael Lang]] \u2013 acoustic piano (2, 9), Fender Rhodes (9)\n* David Cochrane \u2013 [[Sequential Circuits Prophet 5|Prophet 5]] (3), electric guitar (3, 7), synthesizer bass (3, 7), backing vocals (3, 7), arrangements (3, 5), acoustic piano (5), bass guitar (5), saxophone solo (5)\n* [[Michael Boddicker]] \u2013 synthesizer (3, 5, 7), [[vocoder]] (3, 5, 7)\n* [[Bill Payne]] \u2013 Fender Rhodes (6)\n* [[Paul Jackson Jr.]] \u2013 electric guitar (1, 2, 6)\n* [[Fred Tackett]] \u2013 acoustic guitar (2)\n* [[Thomas Dolby]] - Synthesizer, Programming and backing vocals on \u201cYou are\u201d\n* [[Joe Walsh]] \u2013 guitar solo (2)\n* [[Richie Zito]] \u2013 guitar solo (3)\n* Darrell Jones \u2013 electric guitar (4, 5, 7), acoustic guitar (8)\n* Tim May \u2013 acoustic guitar (6)\n* [[Nathan Watts]] \u2013 bass guitar (1)\n* [[Joe Chemay]] \u2013 bass guitar (2, 